  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis â€” jobsquare\n\n**Current state: zero tests exist.** No `tests/` directory, no pytest config, and `pytest`/`respx`/`pytest-asyncio` aren't even in `requirements.txt` (only `httpx` and `PyYAML`). Everything below is therefore a gap. I've grouped findings by module, in priority order (highest risk first), with a skeleton per gap.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` â€” `parse_posted_at` (highest priority, zero coverage, subtle bug surface)\n\n**Untested logic:** epoch-ms vs epoch-s disambiguation, ISO parsing, the `Z` normalization, tz-naive fallback.\n\n**Edge cases missed:**\n- Empty string / `None` â†’ should return `None`\n- Negative epoch (`s.lstrip(\"-\").isdigit()` branch â€” malformed/negative timestamps)\n- Epoch boundary exactly at `1_000_000_000_000` (ms vs s cutoff)\n- ISO string with no tz info (naive) â†’ must be forced to UTC, not left naive\n- Garbage string â†’ `ValueError` caught, returns `None`\n- `Job.content_hash` stability â€” same title/location/url/department â†’ same hash; changing any one of them â†’ different hash\n- `Job.key` uniqueness/stability across repeated construction\n- `to_row()` drops `raw` and adds `key`/`content_hash`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_and_none_return_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None\n\n    def test_epoch_milliseconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\")\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_iso_with_z_suffix(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso_naive_gets_utc_forced(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_unparseable_string_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_negative_number_does_not_crash(self):\n        # lstrip(\"-\").isdigit() accepts \"-5\"; fromtimestamp must not raise\n        result = parse_posted_at(\"-5\")\n        assert result is not None or result is None  # document actual behavior\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **overrides):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                     title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\", location=\"SF\")\n        base.update(overrides)\n        return Job(**base)\n\n    def test_key_is_stable_and_unique(self):\n        j1, j2 = self._job(), self._job(external_id=\"2\")\n        assert j1.key != j2.key\n        assert j1.key == f\"{j1.source}:{j1.company}:{j1.external_id}\"\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title_change(self):\n        j1, j2 = self._job(), self._job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")\n        assert j1.content_hash != j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable_when_irrelevant_field_changes(self):\n        # posted_at/salary_range aren't part of the hash blob\n        j1, j2 = self._job(), self._job(posted_at=\"2024-01-01\")\n        assert j1.content_hash == j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_to_row_drops_raw_and_adds_derived_fields(self):\n        j = self._job(raw={\"secret\": True})\n        row = j.to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n        assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` â€” `match` / `filter_jobs` (pure logic, easy wins, currently 0% covered)\n\n**Edge cases missed:**\n- Word-boundary regex matching (`\\b`) â€” e.g. include `\"ml\"` shouldn't match `\"html\"`\n- Case-insensitivity\n- Exclude takes precedence over include when both match\n- Empty include list = match everything (not \"match nothing\")\n- Location matching is substring/case-insensitive\n- `cutoff` set but `job.posted_dt` unparseable â†’ job is **kept** (documented \"don't nuke\" behavior) â€” this is a deliberate business rule that needs a regression test\n- `max_age_days` as float/string coercion in `filter_jobs`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef make_job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=\"Software Engineer\", url=\"u\", location=\"Remote - US\",\n                department=\"Engineering\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_word_boundary_prevents_substring_false_positive(self):\n        j = make_job(title=\"HTML Developer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"ml\"]) is False\n\n    def test_case_insensitive_include(self):\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"Backend Engineer\"), include=[\"ENGINEER\"])\n\n    def test_exclude_wins_over_include(self):\n        j = make_job(title=\"Senior Staff Engineer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"senior\"]) is False\n\n    def test_no_include_rule_matches_everything(self):\n        assert match(make_job(), include=None) is True\n\n    def test_location_substring_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(make_job(location=\"Remote - United States\"),\n                     locations=[\"united states\"])\n        assert match(make_job(location=\"Berlin\"), locations=[\"united states\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_confirmed_old_job(self):\n        old = make_job(posted_at=\"2020-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)\n        assert match(old, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at(self):\n        j = make_job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")  # Workday-style, unparseable\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n        assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_job_newer_than_cutoff(self):\n        recent = make_job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)\n        assert match(recent, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_max_age_days_builds_cutoff(self):\n        jobs = [make_job(posted_at=\"2000-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {\"max_age_days\": 1}) == []\n\n    def test_no_rules_returns_all(self):\n        jobs = [make_job(), make_job(external_id=\"2\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` â€” `Store` (dedup correctness is the core value prop; zero coverage)\n\n**Untested logic:** first-insert vs unchanged vs changed-content branching in `diff()`, schema migration idempotency, `next_seq` monotonicity/concurrency claim, `added_since` ordering/boundary.\n\n**Edge cases missed:**\n- Same job fetched twice in one `diff()` call in the same batch (duplicate `key` within the list)\n- `_migrate()` on a pre-existing DB file missing `salary_range` â€” additive migration path\n- `added_since` boundary: exactly equal to `ts` must be **excluded** (`>`, not `>=`)\n- `next_seq` starting from 0 when key doesn't exist yet, and incrementing correctly across calls\n- Context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`) actually closes the connection\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nimport pytest\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    s = Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\")\n    yield s\n    s.close()\n\ndef make_job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=\"Engineer\", url=\"u\", location=\"SF\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_new_job_reported_as_new(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_reported_neither(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job()])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_changed_title_reported_as_changed(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")])\n        assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\n    def test_count_reflects_upserts_not_duplicates(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        store.diff([make_job()])  # same key again\n        assert store.count() == 1\n\nclass TestMeta:\n    def test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(self, store):\n        assert store.get_meta(\"nope\") is None\n\n    def test_set_then_get_roundtrip(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v1\"\n\n    def test_set_meta_overwrites(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\nclass TestNextSeq:\n    def test_starts_at_one(self, store):\n        assert store.next_seq(\"counter\") == 1\n\n    def test_increments_monotonically(self, store):\n        assert [store.next_seq(\"counter\") for _ in range(3)] == [1, 2, 3]\n\n    def test_independent_keys_dont_interfere(self, store):\n        store.next_seq(\"a\")\n        assert store.next_seq(\"b\") == 1\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_excludes_rows_at_exact_boundary(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        row = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        assert store.added_since(row[\"first_seen\"]) == []\n\n    def test_orders_oldest_first(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job(external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\")])\n        store.diff([make_job(external_id=\"2\", title=\"B\")])\n        rows = store.added_since(\"1970-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n        assert [r[\"title\"] for r in rows] == [\"A\", \"B\"]\n\nclass TestMigration:\n    def test_migrate_adds_missing_salary_column(self, tmp_path):\n        path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(str(path))\n        conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n            CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n                external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n                department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n                content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        \"\"\")\n        conn.commit(); conn.close()\n        s = Store(path)  # must not raise\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n        s.close()\n\nclass TestContextManager:\n    def test_exit_closes_connection(self, tmp_path):\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n            pass\n        with pytest.raises(sqlite3.ProgrammingError):\n            s.conn.execute(\"SELECT 1\")\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `fetchers.py` â€” the biggest gap by volume (16 ATS integrations, ~880 lines, 0% covered)\n\nThis file has two coverage-critical layers: **pure parsers** (unit-testable with zero mocking) and **fetch orchestration** (needs `httpx` mocking, e.g. via `respx` or `httpx.MockTransport`).\n\n#### 4a. Parser edge cases missed (per-ATS, all pure functions â€” cheap to test):\n- `parse_greenhouse`: missing `location`/`departments` keys entirely\n- `parse_lever`: `_lever_salary` â€” both min/max present vs. only `salaryDescriptionPlain` vs. neither (should be `\"\"`)\n- `parse_ashby`: `isListed is False` jobs must be filtered out; `isListed` missing (should still include)\n- `_extract_ds1` (Google): both regex fallback paths; malformed JSON; empty match\n- `_ds1_posted_at`: no timestamp fields present â†’ `\"\"`; only index 13/14 populated\n- `parse_deshaw`/`parse_twosigma`: dedup-by-id within a single page (`seen` set logic), missing optional fields (no href/location match)\n- `_apple_hydration`: escaped quotes inside the JSON string (the manual quote-scanner is a real bug risk), missing hydration marker\n- `_apple_posted_at`: nanosecond truncation, `None`/empty input\n- `parse_meta`: duplicate ids across the same batch (`seen` dedup)\n- `parse_microsoft`/`parse_netflix`: missing timestamp â†’ `posted_at=\"\"`; multiple location formats (`standardizedLocations` vs `locations`)\n- `_amazon_posted_at`: malformed date string â†’ `\"\"` (must not raise); leap-year date\n- `parse_amazon`: missing both `id` and `id_icims`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (\n    parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n    _extract_ds1, _ds1_posted_at, parse_google, parse_deshaw,\n    _apple_hydration, _apple_posted_at, parse_apple, parse_meta,\n    parse_microsoft, parse_netflix, _amazon_posted_at, parse_amazon,\n)\n\nclass TestParseGreenhouse:\n    def test_missing_location_and_departments(self):\n        jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\"}]})\n        assert jobs[0].location == \"\" and jobs[0].department == \"\"\n\n    def test_empty_jobs_list(self):\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_min_max_present(self):\n        j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000â€“150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_description(self):\n        j = {\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_no_salary_info_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\nclass TestParseAshby:\n    def test_unlisted_jobs_excluded(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False, \"title\": \"Hidden\"},\n                          {\"id\": \"2\", \"title\": \"Visible\"}]}\n        jobs = parse_ashby(\"acme\", data)\n        assert [j.external_id for j in jobs] == [\"2\"]\n\nclass TestExtractDs1:\n    def test_no_match_returns_empty_list(self):\n        assert _extract_ds1(\"<html>no data here</html>\") == []\n\n    def test_fallback_pattern_when_sidechannel_moves(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', ..., data:[[1,2]] });\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == [1, 2]\n\n    def test_malformed_json_returns_empty(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', data:[not valid json], sideChannel\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\nclass TestDs1PostedAt:\n    def test_no_timestamp_fields_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _ds1_posted_at([None] * 12) == \"\"\n\n    def test_uses_first_available_index(self):\n        job = [None] * 13 + [[1700000000, 0]]\n        assert _ds1_posted_at(job).startswith(\"2023\")\n\nclass TestAppleHydration:\n    def test_missing_marker_returns_none(self):\n        assert _apple_hydration(\"<html></html>\") is None\n\n    def test_escaped_quotes_in_payload(self):\n        html = 'window.__staticRouterHydrationData = JSON.parse(\"{\\\\\"a\\\\\":1}\");'\n        assert _apple_hydration(html) == {\"a\": 1}\n\nclass TestApplePostedAt:\n    def test_nanosecond_precision_truncated(self):\n        result = _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:03.812668311Z\")\n        assert result == \"2024-01-15T10:00:03.812668+00:00\"\n\n    def test_empty_input(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_no_fractional_seconds(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:03Z\") == \"2024-01-15T10:00:03+00:00\"\n\nclass TestParseMeta:\n    def test_duplicate_ids_deduped(self):\n        results = [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A\"}, {\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A dup\"}]\n        assert len(parse_meta(\"meta\", results)) == 1\n\n    def test_missing_id_skipped(self):\n        assert parse_meta(\"meta\", [{\"title\": \"No id\"}]) == []\n\nclass TestAmazonPostedAt:\n    def test_valid_date(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_malformed_date_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_empty_string(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n\nclass TestParseAmazon:\n    def test_falls_back_to_id_icims(self):\n        jobs = parse_amazon(\"amazon\", [{\"id_icims\": \"123\", \"title\": \"Eng\", \"job_path\": \"/x\"}])\n        assert jobs[0].external_id == \"123\"\n\n    def test_no_id_at_all(self):\n        jobs = parse_amazon(\"amazon\", [{\"title\": \"Eng\"}])\n        assert jobs[0].external_id == \"\"\n```\n\n#### 4b. Fetch orchestration â€” needs mocked HTTP (currently zero coverage, and this is where retries/pagination/error-swallowing bugs actually live)\n\nRequires adding `respx` (or hand-rolled `httpx.MockTransport`) to `requirements.txt` â€” the file's own docstring says the client is injectable specifically for this reason, but no test exercises it.\n\n**Missing scenarios:**\n- `_request` retry-then-succeed on 429/503, retry exhaustion raising `RuntimeError`, non-retryable 4xx failing immediately\n- Pagination loop termination: `fetch_twosigma`/`fetch_optiver`/`fetch_apple`/`fetch_google`/`fetch_microsoft`/`fetch_netflix`/`fetch_amazon` all share the \"stop when no fresh items\" pattern â€” none is tested for (a) normal multi-page fetch, (b) stopping on empty page, (c) hitting `max_pages` cap\n- `fetch_workday`'s safety cap (`offset > 5000`) and `total`-based termination\n- `fetch_meta`'s `for (;;);` JSONP-guard stripping and its `errors` â†’ `RuntimeError` path (the doc_id-rotation failure mode called out in the module docstring â€” this is exactly the kind of regression a test should catch)\n- `fetch_source` raising `ValueError` for an unknown `ats`\n- `fetch_all`: one source failing must not fail the others (`except Exception` swallow-and-log path), and results are flattened correctly\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_fetch.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nfrom fetchers import (\n    _request, fetch_source, fetch_all, fetch_meta, fetch_workday,\n)\n\ndef mock_client(handler):\n    return httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler))\n\nclass TestRequestRetry:\n    async def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds(self):\n        calls = {\"n\": 0}\n        def handler(request):\n            calls[\"n\"] += 1\n            if calls[\"n\"] < 3:\n                return httpx.Response(503)\n            return httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True})\n        async with mock_client(handler) as client:\n            r = await _request(client, \"https://x/y\", retries=4)\n        assert r.json() == {\"ok\": True} and calls[\"n\"] == 3\n\n    async def test_exhausts_retries_and_raises(self):\n        async with mock_client(lambda r: httpx.Response(500)) as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x/y\", retries=2)\n\n    async def test_non_retryable_4xx_fails_fast(self):\n        calls = {\"n\": 0}\n        def handler(request):\n            calls[\"n\"] += 1\n            return httpx.Response(404)\n        async with mock_client(handler) as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x/y\", retries=4)\n        assert calls[\"n\"] == 1  # no retry on non-retryable status\n\nclass TestFetchSource:\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises_value_error(self):\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n                await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n\nclass TestFetchAll:\n    async def test_one_source_failing_does_not_fail_others(self):\n        def handler(request):\n            if \"greenhouse\" in str(request.url):\n                return httpx.Response(500)\n            return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": []})\n        async with mock_client(handler) as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_all(\n                [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"a\"},\n                 {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"b\"}],\n                client=client,\n            )\n        assert jobs == []  # both empty, but call didn't raise\n\nclass TestFetchMeta:\n    async def test_strips_jsonp_guard_and_parses(self):\n        def handler(request):\n            if request.method == \"POST\":\n                body = 'for (;;);' + '{\"data\":{\"job_search_with_featured_jobs_v2\":{\"all_jobs\":[]}}}'\n                return httpx.Response(200, text=body)\n            return httpx.Response(200, text='\"LSD\",[],{\"token\":\"tok\"} \"__spin_r\":1')\n        async with mock_client(handler) as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_meta(client, {})\n        assert jobs == []\n\n    async def test_graphql_errors_raise_runtime_error(self):\n        def handler(request):\n            if request.method == \"POST\":\n                return httpx.Response(200, json={\"errors\": [{\"message\": \"doc_id invalid\"}]})\n            return httpx.Response(200, text=\"\")\n        async with mock_client(handler) as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"meta graphql\"):\n                await fetch_meta(client, {})\n\nclass TestFetchWorkday:\n    async def test_stops_at_offset_total(self):\n        def handler(request):\n            return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobPostings\": [], \"total\": 0})\n        async with mock_client(handler) as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"h\", \"tenant\": \"t\", \"site\": \"s\"})\n        assert jobs == []\n\n    async def test_pagination_advances_and_stops(self):\n        pages = {\"n\": 0}\n        def handler(request):\n            pages[\"n\"] += 1\n            if pages[\"n\"] == 1:\n                return httpx.Response(200, json={\n                    \"jobPostings\": [{\"title\": \"A\", \"externalPath\": \"/a\",\n                                     \"bulletFields\": [\"REQ1\"]}],\n                    \"total\": 1})\n            return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobPostings\": [], \"total\": 1})\n        async with mock_client(handler) as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"h\", \"tenant\": \"t\", \"site\": \"s\"})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n```\n\nNote: async tests need `pytest-asyncio` (`asyncio_mode = auto` in config) â€” not currently a dependency.\n\n---\n\n### 5. `notify.py` â€” env-var-gated notifiers (0% covered, silent-failure risk)\n\n**Untested logic:** every notifier's \"activate only if env var(s) set\" gate, `dispatch`'s per-notifier exception isolation, `_sms_body` truncation.\n\n**Edge cases missed:**\n- Each notifier: missing env var â†’ no-op (no network call attempted)\n- Each notifier: env var set but `new`/`changed` both empty â†’ no-op (avoid spamming empty notifications)\n- `dispatch`: one notifier raising must not prevent the others from running\n- `_sms_body`: truncation message (`+N more`) when `new` exceeds `limit`\n- `notify_email`: `SMTP_USER` present vs absent (login step skipped)\n- `notify_sms`: `resp.raise_for_status()` propagating on Twilio 4xx (bad credentials)\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nfrom notify import notify_slack, notify_webhook, notify_sms, _sms_body, dispatch\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef make_job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=\"Engineer\", url=\"u\", location=\"SF\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\nclass TestEnvGating:\n    def test_slack_noop_without_webhook_url(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify_slack([make_job()], [])\n        post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_slack_noop_when_nothing_new_or_changed(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks/x\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify_slack([], [])\n        post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_slack_posts_when_configured_and_new(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks/x\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify_slack([make_job()], [])\n        post.assert_called_once()\n\n    def test_sms_requires_all_four_twilio_vars(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify_sms([make_job()], [])\n        post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_sms_propagates_http_error(self, monkeypatch):\n        for k, v in [(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\"), (\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"tok\"),\n                     (\"TWILIO_FROM\", \"+1\"), (\"TWILIO_TO\", \"+2\")]:\n            monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n        resp = MagicMock()\n        resp.raise_for_status.side_effect = Exception(\"401 unauthorized\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\", return_value=resp):\n            with pytest.raises(Exception, match=\"401\"):\n                notify_sms([make_job()], [])\n\nclass TestSmsBody:\n    def test_truncates_with_more_count(self):\n        jobs = [make_job(external_id=str(i), title=f\"Job {i}\") for i in range(10)]\n        body = _sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n        assert \"+2 more\" in body\n\n    def test_no_truncation_marker_under_limit(self):\n        jobs = [make_job(external_id=\"1\")]\n        assert \"more\" not in _sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n\nclass TestDispatch:\n    def test_one_notifier_failing_does_not_block_others(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks/x\")\n        calls = []\n        with patch(\"notify.notify_console\", side_effect=RuntimeError(\"boom\")), \\\n             patch(\"notify.notify_slack\", side_effect=lambda n, c: calls.append(\"slack\")), \\\n             patch(\"notify.notify_webhook\"), patch(\"notify.notify_email\"), \\\n             patch(\"notify.notify_sms\"):\n            dispatch([make_job()], [])\n        assert calls == [\"slack\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `pipeline.py` â€” orchestration (integration-level gap)\n\n**Untested:** `load_config` defaults, `run`'s dry-run short-circuit (must not touch the store), and the full happy-path wiring of fetchâ†’filterâ†’dedupâ†’notify.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nfrom pipeline import load_config, run\n\nclass TestLoadConfig:\n    def test_applies_defaults(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n        cfg = load_config(cfg_path)\n        assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {} and cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n\n    def test_preserves_explicit_values(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(\"db: custom.db\\nconcurrency: 3\\n\")\n        cfg = load_config(cfg_path)\n        assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"custom.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 3\n\nclass TestRun:\n    async def test_dry_run_does_not_touch_store(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\ndb: unused.db\\n\")\n        with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[])), \\\n             patch(\"pipeline.Store\") as store_cls:\n            result = await run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n        store_cls.assert_not_called()\n        assert result == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n\n    async def test_happy_path_calls_dispatch(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path / 'j.db'}\\n\")\n        with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[])), \\\n             patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as dispatch_mock:\n            result = await run(cfg_path)\n        dispatch_mock.assert_called_once()\n        assert result == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `agent.py` â€” deterministic helpers (integration/CLI-level gap)\n\nThe docstring explicitly separates \"deterministic data helpers... no LLM involved\" from the Claude launcher â€” the former is fully unit-testable and untested.\n\n**Missing scenarios:**\n- `cmd_db_new`: first run (no marker â†’ `FIRST_RUN_DAYS` window), subsequent run (marker present), truncation at group boundaries (the `groupby`-by-`first_seen` logic is subtle and worth a dedicated test), `--limit` smaller than one group\n- `cmd_db_mark`: `--now` vs explicit watermark vs invalid ISO string (exit code 2) vs neither arg supplied (exit code 2)\n- `cmd_report_num`: sequential calls increment\n- `_normalize_ats`: each rule in `_ATS_RULES` individually, and crucially that substitutions **don't touch tag attributes or `<style>`/`<script>` contents** (this is the one correctness property that would silently corrupt HTML if broken)\n- `_apple_hydration`-style manual scanning isn't here, but `_chrome_bin()`'s `CHROME_PATH` / `PATH` / hardcoded app fallback chain is untested\n- `main()`'s argv routing: `db-new`/`db-mark`/`pdf-render`/`report-num` dispatch, bare invocation â†’ interactive, mode words vs `-i`/flag passthrough split\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport json\nimport pytest\nfrom agent import cmd_db_mark, _normalize_ats, MARK_KEY\nfrom store import Store\n\nclass TestDbMark:\n    def test_now_sets_current_timestamp(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path / 'j.db'}\\n\")\n        assert cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 0\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"j.db\") as s:\n            assert s.get_meta(MARK_KEY) is not None\n\n    def test_invalid_watermark_exits_2(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path / 'j.db'}\\n\")\n        assert cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\n    def test_no_args_exits_2(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path / 'j.db'}\\n\")\n        assert cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_smart_quotes_replaced_in_body_text(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<p>\\u201cHello\\u201d</p>\")\n        assert html == '<p>\"Hello\"</p>'\n        assert counts.get(\"smart-double-quote\") == 2\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_tag_attributes(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats('<div class=\"foo\\u2014bar\">text</div>')\n        assert 'class=\"foo\\u2014bar\"' in html  # em-dash inside attribute untouched\n        assert counts == {}\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_style_or_script_blocks(self):\n        html = \"<style>.x{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>\\u2014</p>\"\n        out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n        assert \"content:'\\u2014'\" in out          # untouched inside <style>\n        assert counts.get(\"em-dash\") == 1          # only the <p> one counted\n\n    def test_bullet_and_middot_map_to_pipe(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<li>a \\u2022 b \\u00b7 c</li>\")\n        assert html == \"<li>a | b | c</li>\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Integration-test gaps (no single-module test catches these)\n\nNone of the above catches cross-module wiring bugs. Worth at least one true end-to-end test:\n\n```python\n# tests/test_integration.py\nimport respx\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nfrom pipeline import run\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.mark.integration\nasync def test_full_pipeline_dedupes_across_two_runs(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"\"\"\nsources:\n  - ats: greenhouse\n    company: acme\ndb: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\nfilters: {{}}\n\"\"\")\n    payload = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Engineer\",\n                          \"absolute_url\": \"https://x/1\", \"location\": {\"name\": \"SF\"}}]}\n    with respx.mock:\n        respx.get(\"https://boards-api.greenhouse.io/v1/boards/acme/jobs\").respond(\n            json=payload)\n        r1 = await run(cfg_path)\n        r2 = await run(cfg_path)  # second run â€” same job, should dedup\n    assert r1[\"new\"] == 1\n    assert r2[\"new\"] == 0 and r2[\"changed\"] == 0\n```\n\n---\n\n### Recommended setup to make any of this runnable\n\n```\n# add to requirements.txt (or a requirements-dev.txt)\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\nrespx>=0.21\n```\n\n```ini\n# pytest.ini or pyproject.toml [tool.pytest.ini_options]\n[pytest]\nasyncio_mode = auto\n```\n\n**Priority order if scoping incrementally:** `models.py` and `filters.py` first (pure, zero setup, catch real edge-case bugs like the epoch ms/s cutoff and word-boundary matching) â†’ `store.py` (dedup correctness is the whole point of this tool) â†’ `fetchers.py` parsers (cheap, one per ATS, and several already have documented \"defensive because undocumented API\" comments that are exactly where regressions will hide) â†’ `notify.py` (env-gating regressions are easy to introduce silently) â†’ `fetch_*` orchestration + `pipeline.py`/`agent.py` integration tests last, since they need HTTP mocking infrastructure first.\n\nWant me to actually scaffold these as real files under a `tests/` directory and wire up pytest, or was this meant to stay a read-only analysis?\n",
